<HEADLINE>
Spain offers military aid for relief mission in Indonesia
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
JAKARTA, Jan. 13 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Span's foreign minister has been 
in Indonesia since Wednesday to meet President Susilo Bambang 
Yudhoyono for talks on military aid for tsunami-ravaged Aceh, 
local media reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish minister, Miguel Angel Moratinos, met with Vice 
President Jusuf Kalla on Wednesday and discussed the planned 
dispatch of a Spanish navy vessel and 650 troops to Indonesia, The
Jakarta Post newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Forces from a number of countries, including Australia, the 
United States and Japan have scrambled to help with relief efforts
in Aceh, on the northern tip of the Sumatra island, following the 
Dec. 26 disaster.
</P>
<P>
More than 106,500 people were killed in Indonesia by an 8.7-
magnitude earthquake and ensuing tsunami, with almost all the 
deaths occurring in Aceh. Around the Indian Ocean the death toll 
from the disaster stands at more than 158,000.
</P>
